\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Schematic diagram of the electrode design and assembly of the electrochemical cell based on a modified X-band EPR tube. \textbf  {a)} Molecular structure of p-DiTS, with the redox reaction of the charge-bearing TEMPO groups; Highlighted is the backbone, p-NiMeOSalen. \textbf  {b)} Setup for deposition and cleaning of polymer films. \textbf  {c)} Tube-based electrochemical setup. d) Photograph of the modified quartz EPR tube with a flattened bottom section, and the process of forming the modified tube. \textbf  {e)} Cyclic voltammograms of a growing p-DiTS film during 100 electrochemical polymerisation cycles (solid), during the cleaning process (crossed) and in the tube-based setup (dotted). Peaks A/A', B/B' correspond to oxidation and reduction of the TEMPO fragments in p-DiTS and the NiSalen backbone, respectively. All CV were recorded at 50 mV/s.\relax }}{4}\protected@file@percent }
