\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Classification of the nitroxide cwEPR spectra observed for p-DiTS under different conditions and environments. a) Densely packed nitroxide film with exchange and dipolar broadening or exchange narrowing giving a single derivative, b) typical dilute mono-nitroxide in solution spectrum, three-lines due to $S=1/2$ $I=1$ $^{14}N$ hyperfine interaction, c) typical di-nitroxide in solution where dynamic changes in nitroxide distance modulated the exchange interaction giving five lines (actual cwEPR of DiTS monomers in solution at room temperature), d) Immobilized nitroxide spectrum with both $g$ and $A$ (Hyperfine) anisotropy.\relax }}{6}\protected@file@percent }
