\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces \textit  {in-operando} SEC cwEPR of two different p-DiTS films a) 50\nobreakspace  {}CV cycles, (Top) showing the appearance of a superimposed three-line feature, corresponding to mobile nitroxide groups, with increasing oxidation potential. The three-line feature is then electrochemically inactive and remains in during the reduction cycle. The rest electrolyte (Bottom) shows the same three-line feature suggesting release of nitroxide fragments into the electrolyte. b) 200\nobreakspace  {}CV cycles, (Top) showing the appearance of a superimposed three-line feature which is electrochemically active and after oxidation does not re-appear in the reduction cycle, suggesting surface oligomers which are initially mobile but later polymerise to the main film or being released to the electrolyte in the EPR-silent, oxiized state. (Bottom) rest electrolyte shows negligible signal of nitroxide spins.\relax }}{11}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:Figure_5}{{5}{11}}
