\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S4}{\ignorespaces Spin count during the (secondary) release of the monomer from a thick (150 deposition cycles), untreated p-DiTS cell. Before this measurement, the cell has already exhibited the (primary) release of the monomer during the initial charge-discharge cycle, then it was rinsed in Acetonitrile and the electrolyte was exchanged. The three EPR lines in the oxidized cell correspond to the released nitroxide fragments that freely tumble in the electrolyte. a): CwEPR spectra during the charge-discharge cycle of the untreated p-DiTS cell that releases the monomers. b): number of unpaired electrons calculated from the intensities of the cwEPR spectra, considering the non-central position of the cell in the resonator. c) slices of the subplot a), two component simulations and the dry film (measured in the center of the resonator, without electrolyte).\relax }}{23}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S8}{{S4}{23}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {subsection}{\numberline {5.5}Affection of the Q factor by spectrometer parameters}{23}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S5}{\ignorespaces Spin count during the re-polymerization of a thick (200 deposition cycles), cleaned p-DiTS cell. The cell initially exhibits single broad line but at moderate potentials the sattelite lines are formed. The formation of the three sattelite lines is shown in detail in Figure S6\hbox {}. The three EPR lines in the oxidized cell correspond to the released nitroxide fragments that freely tumble in the electrolyte. During the reduction, the satellite peaks disappear and the line broadens. a): CwEPR spectra during the charge-discharge cycle of the cleaned p-DiTS cell that releases the monomers and polymerizes back. b): number of unpaired electrons calculated from the intensities of the cwEPR spectra, considering the non-central position of the cell in the resonator. c) slices of the subplot a), two component simulations and the dry film (measured in the center of the resonator, without electrolyte).\relax }}{24}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S8_SI}{{S5}{24}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S6}{\ignorespaces pDiTS operando redox at RT. Re-polymerisation. Two component fits. Component decomposition. No nitroxide fragments in the used electrolyte.\relax }}{25}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S8_SI}{{S6}{25}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S7}{\ignorespaces pDiTS operando redox at RT. Fits. Component decomposition. BG.\relax }}{26}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S2}{{S7}{26}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S8}{\ignorespaces Initial release of DiTS from an untreated film to the electrolyte.\relax }}{27}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:Figure3_SI}{{S8}{27}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S9}{\ignorespaces Potential-dependent ex situ cwEPR measurements (X-Band, 9.4$\,$GHz) on a dry, frozen p-DiTS film at 150K. Decomposition of spectral lines into two components with numeric simulations: a broad lorentzian line (g = 2.0070, lw = 4.63$\pm $1.00$\,$mT) and a dilute component with a hyperfine coupling to $^{14}$N (I = 1, g = [2.00231 2.00711 2.00912], A = [100 15 15]$\pm $[1 5 5]$\,$MHz, Lorentzian broadening with lw = 1.65$\,$mT). The absorption profiles are shown with the integrals of the EPR signals. The ratio between the simulated components for each potential is shown by the double integrals of the components. Inset: sum of the broad and dilute components that reproduce the line shape at 0.6$\,$V. \relax }}{28}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:S4}{{S9}{28}}
